🏗️ PDF Inspection → DDR Generator

This project automates the generation of a Detailed Diagnostic Report (DDR) from two types of PDFs:

Inspection Report
Thermal Report

It extracts text and images, structures the data using an LLM, merges insights, and generates a professional, client-friendly diagnostic report.

🚀 Features
📄 Extract text from PDFs
🖼️ Extract images from PDFs
🤖 Use Gemini LLM to structure observations
🔗 Merge inspection + thermal insights
📝 Generate a complete DDR report
✅ Data validation using Pydantic
🧰 Tech Stack
Python 3.12
pdfplumber – text extraction
PyMuPDF (fitz) – image extraction
google-generativeai – Gemini LLM
pydantic – schema validation
📦 Installation
pip install pdfplumber pymupdf google-generativeai pydantic
🔑 Setup

Configure your Gemini API key:

import google.generativeai as genai

genai.configure(api_key="YOUR_API_KEY")
model = genai.GenerativeModel("gemini-2.5-flash")
🧱 Data Model
class Observation(BaseModel):
    area: str
    issue: str
    temperature: str
    source: str
⚙️ Pipeline Overview
1. Text Extraction

Extracts text from PDFs using pdfplumber.

2. Image Extraction

Extracts images using PyMuPDF.

3. Structuring Data (LLM)
Converts raw text into structured JSON
Uses Gemini for intelligent parsing
Enforces clean output format
4. Data Merging
Combines inspection and thermal observations
Matches by area
Merges issues and fills missing temperature data
5. DDR Generation

Creates a structured report with:

Property Issue Summary
Area-wise Observations
Probable Root Cause
Severity Assessment
Recommended Actions
Additional Notes
Missing or Unclear Information
▶️ Usage
Upload PDFs (Google Colab)
from google.colab import files
uploaded = files.upload()
Run Pipeline
report = run_pipeline("inspection.pdf", "thermal.pdf")
print(report)
📄 Output
DDR_Report.txt → Final generated report
Extracted images saved in local folders
⚠️ Important Notes
PDFs should contain selectable text (not purely scanned)
JSON extraction uses regex and may require tuning for edge cases
Missing temperature values default to "Not Available"
Do not hardcode API keys in production environments
